"{\"uid\": \"cbc.ca-news-politics-paris-olympics-cyber-warning-cse-1.7220499\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"As athletes and officials prepare for this summer's Paris Olympics, Canada's electronic intelligence agency is warning them to also get ready for likely cyberattacks.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 166, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 52, \"end\": 66, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 68, \"end\": 74, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.158060689662271e-13, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Communications Security Establishment (CSE)\\u00a0-\\u00a0in charge of gathering signals intelligence and protecting the federal government's cyber networks\\u00a0- issued a threat bulletin Friday morning aimed at tourists, government officials and athletes attending the events, as well as Canadian organizations involved in organizing, managing, sponsoring and broadcasting major sporting events.\", \"from\": 168, \"to\": 552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 172, \"end\": 209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Communications Security Establishment\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\"}, {\"begin\": 211, \"end\": 214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3114297183834375e-34, \"text\": \"CSE\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\"}, {\"begin\": 445, \"end\": 453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9988732099508913, \"rank\": 0.0009156678561942789, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The high profile and costly nature of major international sporting events make them a prime target for cybercriminals looking to exploit targets of opportunity for profit.\", \"from\": 554, \"to\": 726, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They also provide a global stage for hacktivists and state-sponsored actors to gather information and publicly embarrass a target,\\\" thereport says.\", \"from\": 727, \"to\": 874, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sami Khoury, head of CSE's Canadian Centre for Cyber Security, said the Olympics, this summer's\\u00a0Formula 1 Canadian Grand Prix in Montreal\\u00a0and the World Junior Championships in Ottawa this winter are all ripe for \\\"cyber malfeasance.\\\"\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 1108, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 876, \"end\": 880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sami_Brady\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9160104329960944e-18, \"text\": \"Sami\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sami_Brady\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sami_Brady\"}, {\"begin\": 881, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elias_Khoury\", \"score\": 0.9030624868344221, \"rank\": 0.10734308486799747, \"text\": \"Khoury\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elias_Khoury\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elias_Khoury\"}, {\"begin\": 897, \"end\": 900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3114297183834375e-34, \"text\": \"CSE\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\"}, {\"begin\": 903, \"end\": 911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9988732099508913, \"rank\": 0.0009156678561942789, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 1005, \"end\": 1013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"score\": 0.9999999921701601, \"rank\": 7.812439872850872e-09, \"text\": \"Montreal\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\"}, {\"begin\": 1022, \"end\": 1048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IIHF_World_Junior_Championship\", \"score\": 0.8965234812641834, \"rank\": 0.1152635042551826, \"text\": \"World Junior Championships\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IIHF_World_Junior_Championship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IIHF_World_Junior_Championship\"}, {\"begin\": 1052, \"end\": 1058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ottawa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.32731553352939e-16, \"text\": \"Ottawa\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ottawa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ottawa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The CSE bulletin said cybercriminals \\\"will very likely target\\\" for extortion large organizations - such as government organizations and corporations involved in sponsoring the events -\\u00a0and local businesses, especially those in the travel and hospitality sectors.\", \"from\": 1110, \"to\": 1372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1114, \"end\": 1117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3114297183834375e-34, \"text\": \"CSE\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Attendees and spectators should also be aware they could be targeted through\\u00a0phishing emails and malicious websites, the agency said.\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Topical event-related lures may include promises of discounted merchandise, free event tickets or access to a livestream of the events,\\\" the report says.\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1663, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"CSE said state-sponsored cyber threat actors likely will try to spy on prominent and high-profile individuals, including representatives of government and anti-doping organziations.\", \"from\": 1665, \"to\": 1846, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1665, \"end\": 1668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3114297183834375e-34, \"text\": \"CSE\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We know that these events, especially\\u00a0[the] opening ceremony, closing ceremony, tend to draw a lot of very important people to those events, heads of states, you know, senior government officials.\", \"from\": 1848, \"to\": 2045, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And that's a very rich target for a nation state,\\\" said Khoury.\", \"from\": 2046, \"to\": 2109, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2102, \"end\": 2108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elias_Khoury\", \"score\": 0.9030624868344221, \"rank\": 0.10734308486799747, \"text\": \"Khoury\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elias_Khoury\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elias_Khoury\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said state actors will be looking to\\u00a0collect foreign intelligence or personal information on dignitaries and create a backdoor on their phones to obtain access to their office systems.\", \"from\": 2111, \"to\": 2298, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If\\u00a0I go to Paris, a state sponsored [actor] then exploits my phone.\", \"from\": 2300, \"to\": 2368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2312, \"end\": 2317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999622105, \"rank\": 3.781050958098674e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I come back to work, I am now connected to my IT infrastructure at work and and this is an easy way for a state sponsor to get into our IT without\\u00a0having to maybe exploit the it from the outside,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2574, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The CSE report points to the\\u00a02016 Olympics in Rio, where\\u00a0Russia-backed threat actors targeted\\u00a0hotel chain wi-fi networks and routers used by Olympics officials for reconnaissance.\", \"from\": 2576, \"to\": 2755, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2580, \"end\": 2583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3114297183834375e-34, \"text\": \"CSE\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\"}, {\"begin\": 2605, \"end\": 2618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.861981409021185e-19, \"text\": \"2016 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2622, \"end\": 2625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Earth_Summit\", \"score\": 0.8234957048649733, \"rank\": 0.1455881841077775, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Earth_Summit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Earth_Summit\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were ultimately able to compromise\\u00a0the World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA) databaseand leaked the personal information of 127 athletes, including their test reports, therapeutic use exemptions and past infractions.\", \"from\": 2757, \"to\": 2972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2801, \"end\": 2832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hacktvists likely will also see this summer's\\u00a0Olympics as an opportunity to get their messages out through website defacements, distributed denial-of-service (DDoS) attacks and hack-and-leak operations, said CSE.\", \"from\": 2974, \"to\": 3186, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3182, \"end\": 3185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3114297183834375e-34, \"text\": \"CSE\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Major international sporting events provide an opportunity for hacktivists to widely promote their messaging on domestic issues, environmental causes or international conflict situations,\\\" it said.\", \"from\": 3188, \"to\": 3386, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The threat report said the anti-government protests in France regarding changes to the minimum pension age are \\\"likely a motivation for domestic hacktivism against the 2024 Paris Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 3388, \"to\": 3577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3443, \"end\": 3449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9978150009081147, \"rank\": 0.001864232734888434, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's support for Ukraine has also motivated pro-Russian hacktivist groups, said the report.\", \"from\": 3579, \"to\": 3674, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3579, \"end\": 3585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9978150009081147, \"rank\": 0.001864232734888434, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3600, \"end\": 3607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1585850439880404e-13, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Khoury said events in Canada might attract different threats.\", \"from\": 3676, \"to\": 3737, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3676, \"end\": 3682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elias_Khoury\", \"score\": 0.9030624868344221, \"rank\": 0.10734308486799747, \"text\": \"Khoury\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elias_Khoury\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elias_Khoury\"}, {\"begin\": 3698, \"end\": 3704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.158060689662271e-13, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"French politics are different than Canadian politics,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3739, \"to\": 3803, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3740, \"end\": 3746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9992792616331216, \"rank\": 0.0004476804506166365, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3775, \"end\": 3792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Politics_of_Canada\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canadian politics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Politics_of_Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Politics_of_Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They are hosting an event so there might be cyber activity that is specific to to France, which might be different than maybe when we host the junior hockey in December.\\\"\", \"from\": 3804, \"to\": 3975, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3887, \"end\": 3893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9978150009081147, \"rank\": 0.001864232734888434, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The CSE report ends by\\u00a0encouraging\\u00a0all attendees, athletes, government officials and organizations associated with major international sporting events to take appropriate measures to protect their systems against\\u00a0cyber threats.\", \"from\": 3977, \"to\": 4204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3981, \"end\": 3984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3114297183834375e-34, \"text\": \"CSE\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communications_Security_Establishment\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reporter  Catharine Tunney is a reporter with CBC's Parliament Hill bureau, where she covers national security and the RCMP.\", \"from\": 4206, \"to\": 4330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4226, \"end\": 4232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gene_Tunney\", \"score\": 0.9999999786978153, \"rank\": 2.1302100124441197e-08, \"text\": \"Tunney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gene_Tunney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gene_Tunney\"}, {\"begin\": 4252, \"end\": 4255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"score\": 0.5773370620479473, \"rank\": 0.7320589391056211, \"text\": \"CBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\"}, {\"begin\": 4258, \"end\": 4273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_Hill\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4491531586062012e-41, \"text\": \"Parliament Hill\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_Hill\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_Hill\"}, {\"begin\": 4325, \"end\": 4329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Canadian_Mounted_Police\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3314733011967083e-16, \"text\": \"RCMP\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Canadian_Mounted_Police\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Canadian_Mounted_Police\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She worked previously for CBC in Nova Scotia.\", \"from\": 4331, \"to\": 4376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4357, \"end\": 4360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"score\": 0.5773370620479473, \"rank\": 0.7320589391056211, \"text\": \"CBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\"}, {\"begin\": 4364, \"end\": 4375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nova_Scotia\", \"score\": 0.999999998117346, \"rank\": 1.882719000412259e-09, \"text\": \"Nova Scotia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nova_Scotia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nova_Scotia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can reach her at catharine.tunney@cbc.ca  Add some \\\"good\\\" to your morning and evening.\", \"from\": 4377, \"to\": 4467, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your guide to what you need to know about the 2025 federal election.\", \"from\": 4469, \"to\": 4537, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Get the latest news and sharp analysis from the campaign trail delivered to your inbox six mornings a week.\", \"from\": 4538, \"to\": 4645, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The next issue of Canada Votes 2025 will soon be in your inbox.Discover all CBC newsletters in theSubscription Centre.\", \"from\": 4647, \"to\": 4765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4665, \"end\": 4671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.158060689662271e-13, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 4723, \"end\": 4726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"score\": 0.5773370620479473, \"rank\": 0.7320589391056211, \"text\": \"CBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and the GooglePrivacy Policyand GoogleTerms of Serviceapply.\", \"from\": 4767, \"to\": 4863, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Audience Relations, CBCP.O.\", \"from\": 4865, \"to\": 4892, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Box 500 Station AToronto, ONCanada, M5W 1E6  Toll-free (Canada only):1-866-306-4636  It is a priority for CBC to create products that are accessible to all in Canada including people with visual, hearing, motor and cognitive challenges.\", \"from\": 4893, \"to\": 5129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4999, \"end\": 5002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"score\": 0.5773370620479473, \"rank\": 0.7320589391056211, \"text\": \"CBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\"}, {\"begin\": 5052, \"end\": 5058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.158060689662271e-13, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Closed Captioning and Described Video is available for many CBC shows offered onCBC Gem.\", \"from\": 5131, \"to\": 5219, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5131, \"end\": 5148, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Closed_captioning\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Closed Captioning\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Closed_captioning\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Closed_captioning\"}, {\"begin\": 5191, \"end\": 5194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"score\": 0.5773370620479473, \"rank\": 0.7320589391056211, \"text\": \"CBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation\"}]}]}"